#. Tag: title
#: microbe.docbook:3
#, no-c-format
msgid "&microbe;"
msgstr "&microbe;"

#. Tag: title
#: microbe.docbook:5
#, no-c-format
msgid "Introduction and General Syntax"
msgstr "Inledning och generell syntax"

#. Tag: para
#: microbe.docbook:6
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<application>Microbe</application> compiles programs written in the custom "
"language for PICs, as a companion program to &ktechlab;. The syntax has been "
"designed to suit a &flowcode; program. The syntax for running "
"<command>microbe</command> from the command line is: <programlisting>microbe "
"[options] [input.microbe] [output.asm]</programlisting> where options are:"
msgstr ""
"<application>Microbe</application> kompilerar program skrivna i språket "
"anpassat för PIC:er, som ett medföljande program till &ktechlab;. Syntaxen "
"har skapats för att passa ett &flowcode;-program. Syntaxen för att köra "
"<command>microbe</command> på kommandoraden är: <programlisting>microbe "
"[väljare] [indata.microbe] [utdata.asm]</programlisting> där väljare är:"

#. Tag: para
#: microbe.docbook:16
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<function>--show-source</function> - Puts each line of &microbe; source code "
"as a comment in the assembly output before the assembly instructions "
"themselves for that line."
msgstr ""
"<function>--show-source</function>: Lägger till varje &microbe;-källkodsrad  "
"som en kommentar i assemblerutmatningen innan själva "
"assemblerinstruktionerna för den raden."

#. Tag: para
#: microbe.docbook:17
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<function>--no-optimize</function> - Prevent optimization of the "
"instructions generated from the source. Optimization is usually safe, and so "
"this option is mainly used for debugging."
msgstr ""
"<function>--no-optimize</function>: Förhindra optimering av instruktionerna "
"skapade från källkoden. Optimering är oftast säker, alltså är väljaren i "
"huvudsak avsedd för avlusning."

#. Tag: para
#: microbe.docbook:20
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The .microbe input file must identify the target PIC by inserting the PIC "
"name at the top of the .microbe file; &eg; the name of a PIC16F84 is "
"\"P16F84\"."
msgstr ""
"Filen indata.microbe måste identifiera PIC:n som är målet genom att infoga "
"namnet på PIC:n längst upp i filen, t.ex. är namnet på PIC16F84 \"P16F84\"."

#. Tag: title
#: microbe.docbook:23
#, no-c-format
msgid "Simple complete &microbe; program"
msgstr "Enkelt fullständig &microbe;-program"

#. Tag: programlisting
#: microbe.docbook:24
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"P16F84\n"
"\n"
"a = 0\n"
"repeat\n"
"{\n"
"        PORTA = a\n"
"        a = a + 1\n"
"}\n"
"until a == 5\n"
"\n"
"end"
msgstr ""
"P16F84\n"
"\n"
"a = 0\n"
"repeat\n"
"{\n"
"        PORTA = a\n"
"        a = a + 1\n"
"}\n"
"until a == 5\n"
"\n"
"end"

#. Tag: title
#: microbe.docbook:29
#, no-c-format
msgid "Naming conventions"
msgstr "Namngivningskonventioner"

#. Tag: para
#: microbe.docbook:30
#, no-c-format
msgid "The following rules apply to variable names and labels:"
msgstr "Följande regler gäller för variabelnamn och etiketter:"

#. Tag: para
#: microbe.docbook:33
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"They can only contain alphanumerical characters [a..z][A..Z][0..9] and the "
"underscore \"_\"."
msgstr ""
"De kan bara innehålla alfanumeriska tecken [a..z][A..Z][0..9] och "
"understrecket \"_\"."

#. Tag: para
#: microbe.docbook:34
#, no-c-format
msgid "They are case-sensitive."
msgstr "De är skiftlägeskänsliga."

#. Tag: para
#: microbe.docbook:35
#, no-c-format
msgid "They cannot start with a number."
msgstr "De kan inte börja med en siffra."

#. Tag: para
#: microbe.docbook:36
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"They should not start with <quote>__</quote> (double underscore), as this is "
"reserved for use by the compiler."
msgstr ""
"De får inte börja med <quote>__</quote> (dubbla understreck) eftersom det är "
"reserverat för användning av kompilatorn."

#. Tag: title
#: microbe.docbook:42
#, no-c-format
msgid "Bracing conventions"
msgstr "Parenteskonventioner"

#. Tag: para
#: microbe.docbook:43
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Curly braces, {}, indicate the start and end of a code block. They can "
"appear anywhere before the start and after the end of the code block. "
"Examples of acceptable code blocks:"
msgstr ""
"Klammerparenteser, {}, anger början och slutet på ett kodblock. De kan "
"finnas var som helst före början och efter slutet på kodblocket. Exempel på "
"korrekta kodblock:"

#. Tag: programlisting
#: microbe.docbook:49
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"statement1 {\n"
"        some code\n"
"}"
msgstr ""
"sats1 {\n"
"        någon kod\n"
"}"

#. Tag: programlisting
#: microbe.docbook:50
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"statement2 {\n"
"        other code }"
msgstr ""
"sats2 {\n"
"        annan kod }"

#. Tag: programlisting
#: microbe.docbook:52
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"statement3\n"
"{\n"
"        other code\n"
"}"
msgstr ""
"sats3\n"
"{\n"
"        annan kod\n"
"}"

#. Tag: programlisting
#: microbe.docbook:54
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"statement5 {\n"
"        code block\n"
"} statement6"
msgstr ""
"sats5 {\n"
"        kodblock\n"
"} sats6"

#. Tag: title
#: microbe.docbook:58
#, no-c-format
msgid "Commenting"
msgstr "Kommentarer"

#. Tag: para
#: microbe.docbook:59
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Commenting is similar to C. // comments out the rest of the line. /* and */ "
"denote a multiline comment."
msgstr ""
"Kommentarer liknar C. // kommenterar bort resten av raden. /* och */ anger "
"en flerraders kommentar."

#. Tag: programlisting
#: microbe.docbook:61
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"// This is a comment\n"
"x = 2 \n"
"/* As is this\n"
"multiline comment */"
msgstr ""
"// Det här är en kommentar\n"
"x = 2 \n"
"/* Liksom denna\n"
"flerraders kommentar */"

#. Tag: title
#: microbe.docbook:66
#, no-c-format
msgid "Program Structure"
msgstr "Programstruktur"

#. Tag: para
#: microbe.docbook:67
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The PIC id must be inserted at the top of the program. The end of the main "
"program is denoted with <quote>end</quote>. Subroutines must placed after "
"<quote>end</quote>."
msgstr ""
"PIC-id måste infogas överst i programmet. Slutet på huvudprogrammet anges "
"med <quote>end</quote>. Subrutiner måste placeras efter <quote>end</quote>."

#. Tag: title
#: microbe.docbook:73
#, no-c-format
msgid "Subroutines"
msgstr "Subrutiner"

#. Tag: para
#: microbe.docbook:74
#, no-c-format
msgid "A subroutine can be called from anywhere in the code. Syntax:"
msgstr "En subrutin kan anropas var som helst i koden. Syntax:"

#. Tag: programlisting
#: microbe.docbook:77
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"sub SubName\n"
"{\n"
"        // Code...\n"
"}"
msgstr ""
"sub SubrutinNamn\n"
"{\n"
"        // Kod...\n"
"}"

#. Tag: para
#: microbe.docbook:78
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The subroutine is called with <quote>call <replaceable>SubName</"
"replaceable></quote>."
msgstr ""
"Subrutinen anropas med <quote>call <replaceable>SubrutinNamn</replaceable></"
"quote>."

#. Tag: title
#: microbe.docbook:83
#, no-c-format
msgid "&microbe; language reference"
msgstr "&microbe; språkreferens"

#. Tag: title
#: microbe.docbook:85 microbe.docbook:99
#, no-c-format
msgid "<title>if</title>"
msgstr "<title>if</title>"

#. Tag: para
#: microbe.docbook:86
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Conditional branching. Syntax: <programlisting role=\"correct\">if "
"[expression] then [statement]</programlisting> or <programlisting role="
"\"correct\">\n"
"if [expression] then\n"
"{\n"
"        [statement block]\n"
"}</programlisting> Similarly for else: <programlisting role=\"correct\">else "
"[statement]</programlisting> or"
msgstr ""
"Villkorliga hopp. Syntax: <programlisting role=\"correct\">if [uttryck] then "
"[sats]</programlisting> eller <programlisting role=\"correct\">\n"
"if [uttryck] then\n"
"{\n"
"        [satsblock]\n"
"}</programlisting> På liknande sätt för else: <programlisting role=\"correct"
"\">else [sats]</programlisting> eller"

#. Tag: programlisting
#: microbe.docbook:96
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"else\n"
"{\n"
"        [statement block]\n"
"}"
msgstr ""
"else\n"
"{\n"
"        [satsblock]\n"
"}"

#. Tag: programlisting
#: microbe.docbook:100
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"if porta.0 is high then\n"
"{\n"
"        delay 200\n"
"}\n"
"else\n"
"{\n"
"        delay 300\n"
"}"
msgstr ""
"if porta.0 is high then\n"
"{\n"
"        delay 200\n"
"}\n"
"else\n"
"{\n"
"        delay 300\n"
"}"

#. Tag: title
#: microbe.docbook:105
#, no-c-format
msgid "alias"
msgstr "alias"

#. Tag: para
#: microbe.docbook:106
#, no-c-format
msgid "Aliases one string to another. Syntax:"
msgstr "Skapar ett alias från en sträng till en annan. Syntax:"

#. Tag: programlisting
#: microbe.docbook:107
#, no-c-format
msgid "alias [from] [to]"
msgstr "alias [från] [till]"

#. Tag: title
#: microbe.docbook:112
#, no-c-format
msgid "repeat"
msgstr "repeat"

#. Tag: para
#: microbe.docbook:113
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Executes the statement block repeatedly until expression evaluates to true. "
"The evaluation of the expression is performed after the statement block, so "
"the statement block will always be executed at least once. Syntax:"
msgstr ""
"Kör satsblocket upprepade gånger tills uttrycket utvärderas till true. "
"Utvärderingen av uttrycket utförs efter satsblocket, så att satsblocket "
"alltid körs minst en gång. Syntax:"

#. Tag: programlisting
#: microbe.docbook:116
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"repeat\n"
"{\n"
"        [statement block]\n"
"}\n"
"until [expression]"
msgstr ""
"repeat\n"
"{\n"
"        [satsblock]\n"
"}\n"
"until [uttryck]"

#. Tag: title
#: microbe.docbook:121
#, no-c-format
msgid "while"
msgstr "while"

#. Tag: para
#: microbe.docbook:122
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Similar to repeat, this repeatedly executes the statement block. However, "
"the expression is evaluated before execution, not after. So if the "
"expression evaluates to false on the first pass, then the statement block "
"will not get executed. Syntax:"
msgstr ""
"Liksom repeat, kör det satsblocket upprepade gånger. Dock utvärderas "
"uttrycket innan körning, inte efter. Om uttrycket alltså utvärderas till "
"false den första gången, körs inte satsblocket. Syntax:"

#. Tag: programlisting
#: microbe.docbook:126
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"while [expression]\n"
"{\n"
"        [statement block]\n"
"}"
msgstr ""
"while [uttryck]\n"
"{\n"
"        [satsblock]\n"
"}"

#. Tag: title
#: microbe.docbook:132 microbe.docbook:145
#, no-c-format
msgid "goto"
msgstr "goto"

#. Tag: para
#: microbe.docbook:133
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"This causes execution of the code to continue at the next statement after "
"the label specified. Goto syntax: <programlisting role=\"correct"
"\"><function>goto</function> [labelname]</programlisting> Label syntax: "
"<programlisting role=\"correct\"><function>labelname:</function></"
"programlisting> It is often considered good programming practice to avoid "
"the use of goto. Use of control statements and subroutines will result in a "
"much more readable program."
msgstr ""
"Gör att körning av koden fortsätter med nästa sats efter den angivna "
"etiketten. Syntax för goto: <programlisting role=\"correct\"><function>goto</"
"function> [etikettnamn]</programlisting> Etikettsyntax: <programlisting role="
"\"correct\"><function>etikettnamn:</function></programlisting> Det är ofta "
"god programmeringsvana att undvika användning av goto. Användning av "
"kontrollsatser och subrutiner leder till ett mycket mer läsbart program."

#. Tag: programlisting
#: microbe.docbook:146
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"goto MyLabel\n"
"\n"
"...\n"
"\n"
"[MyLabel]:\n"
"// Code will continue at this point"
msgstr ""
"goto MinEtikett\n"
"\n"
"...\n"
"\n"
"[MinEtikett]:\n"
"// Koden fortsätter på det här stället"

#. Tag: title
#: microbe.docbook:151
#, no-c-format
msgid "call"
msgstr "call"

#. Tag: para
#: microbe.docbook:152
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Calls a subroutine. Syntax: <programlisting role=\"correct\"><function>call</"
"function> [SubName]</programlisting> where <replaceable>SubName</"
"replaceable> is the name of the subroutine to be called."
msgstr ""
"Anropar en subrutin. Syntax: <programlisting role=\"correct"
"\"><function>call</function> [SubrutinNamn]</programlisting> där "
"<replaceable>SubrutinNamn</replaceable> är namnet på subrutinen som ska "
"anropas."

#. Tag: title
#: microbe.docbook:162
#, no-c-format
msgid "delay"
msgstr "delay"

#. Tag: para
#: microbe.docbook:163
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"This causes the code execution to stop for the given period of time. The "
"interval is in milliseconds. Syntax:"
msgstr ""
"Gör att körning av koden stoppas under angiven tidsperiod. Intervallet anges "
"i millisekunder. Syntax:"

#. Tag: programlisting
#: microbe.docbook:167
#, no-c-format
msgid "<function>delay</function> [interval]"
msgstr "<function>delay</function> [intervall]"

#. Tag: para
#: microbe.docbook:169
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"At present, &microbe; assumes that the PIC is operating at a frequency of "
"4MHz - &ie; each instruction takes 1 microsecond to execute. If this is not "
"the case, the interval must be adjusted proportionately."
msgstr ""
"För närvarande antar &microbe; att PIC:n använder frekvensen 4 MHz, dvs. "
"varje instruktion tar 1 mikrosekund att köra. Om det inte är fallet, måste "
"intervallet justeras proportionellt."

#. Tag: title
#: microbe.docbook:174
#, no-c-format
msgid "sevenseg"
msgstr "sevenseg"

#. Tag: para
#: microbe.docbook:175
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"This is used to define the pin mapping for a (common cathode) seven segment "
"display connected to the PIC. Syntax: <programlisting role=\"correct"
"\"><function>sevenseg</function> [name] [a] [b] [c] [d] [e] [f] [g]</"
"programlisting> where [a]...[g] are the PIC pins to which the respective "
"segments of the seven segment display are attached. The pins can be written "
"either as PORTX.N or RXN."
msgstr ""
"Används för att definiera anslutningsavbildningen för en 7-segmentsdisplay "
"(med gemensam katod) ansluten till PIC:n. Syntax <programlisting role="
"\"correct\"><function>sevenseg</function> [namn] [a] [b] [c] [d] [e] [f] "
"[g]</programlisting> där [a] ... [g] är PIC:ns anslutningar dit respektive "
"segment i 7-segmentsdisplayen är kopplade. Anslutningarna kan antingen "
"skrivas som PORTX.N eller RXN."

#. Tag: para
#: microbe.docbook:181
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"To display a number on the seven segment, the pin mapping is treated as a "
"write only variable."
msgstr ""
"För att visa ett tal på 7-segmentdisplayen, behandlas "
"anslutningsavbildningen som en enbart skrivbar variabel."

#. Tag: title
#: microbe.docbook:183
#, no-c-format
msgid "Defining and outputting to a seven segment"
msgstr "Definiera och skriva ut på en 7-segmentsdisplay"

#. Tag: programlisting
#: microbe.docbook:184
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"sevenseg seg1 RB0 RB1 RB2 RB3 RB4 RB5 RB6\n"
"seg1 = x + 2"
msgstr ""
"sevenseg seg1 RB0 RB1 RB2 RB3 RB4 RB5 RB6\n"
"seg1 = x + 2"

#. Tag: title
#: microbe.docbook:190
#, no-c-format
msgid "keypad"
msgstr "keypad"

#. Tag: para
#: microbe.docbook:191
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"This is used to define the pin mapping for a keypad connected to the PIC. "
"Syntax: <programlisting role=\"correct\"><function>keypad</function> [name] "
"[row 1] ... [row 4] [column 1] ... [column n]</programlisting> where [row "
"1] ... [row 4] and [column 1] ... [column n] are the PIC pins to which the "
"respective rows and columns of the keypad are attached (at the moment, the "
"number of rows is not changeable). See <xref linkend=\"sevenseg\"/> (above) "
"for more information on pin mappings."
msgstr ""
"Används för att definiera anslutningsavbildningen för en knappsats ansluten "
"till PIC:n. Syntax: <programlisting role=\"correct\"><function>keypad</"
"function> [namn] [rad 1] ... [rad 4] [kolumn 1] ... [kolumn n]</"
"programlisting> där [rad 1] ... [rad 4] och [kolumn 1] ... [kolumn n] är PIC:"
"ns anslutningar dit respektive rad och kolumn på knappsatsen är kopplade "
"(för närvarande kan inte antal rader ändras). Se <xref linkend=\"sevenseg\"/"
"> (ovan) för mer information om anslutningsavbildningar."

#. Tag: para
#: microbe.docbook:197
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The columns of the keypad should be pulled down via 100k resistors to "
"ground. The row pins must be configured as outputs and the column pins as "
"inputs. Once the keypad has been defined, it is treated as a read only "
"variable."
msgstr ""
"Knappsatsens kolumner ska använda ett 100k pull-down motstånd till jord. "
"Radanslutningarna måste vara konfigurerade som utgångar och "
"kolumnanslutningarna som ingångar. När knappsatsen väl har definierats, "
"behandlas den som en enbart läsbar variabel."

#. Tag: title
#: microbe.docbook:199
#, no-c-format
msgid "Defining and reading from a keypad"
msgstr "Definiera och läsa från en knappsats"

#. Tag: programlisting
#: microbe.docbook:200
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"keypad keypad1 RB0 RB1 RB2 RB3 RB4 RB5 RB6\n"
"x = keypad1"
msgstr ""
"keypad keypad1 RB0 RB1 RB2 RB3 RB4 RB5 RB6\n"
"x = keypad1"

#. Tag: para
#: microbe.docbook:204
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"By default, the values returned for a keypad are: <itemizedlist> "
"<listitem><para>The value of the number if it is a numeric key (1 to 3 along "
"top row; hexadecimal A to D down the fourth column and continuing for each "
"extra column).</para></listitem> <listitem><para>253 for the key in row 4, "
"column 1.</para></listitem> <listitem><para>254 for the key in row 4, column "
"3.</para></listitem> </itemizedlist> These values can be redefined by using "
"the alias command, where the name of the key in row x, column y (rows and "
"columns starting at 1), is Keypad_x_y. For example, to give the star key on "
"a 4x3 keypad the value zero, the following alias would be used:"
msgstr ""
"Normalt är värdena som returneras för en knappsats: <itemizedlist> "
"<listitem><para>Värdet på siffran om det är en sifferknapp (1 till 3 längs "
"övre raden, hexadecimalt A till D längs den fjärde kolumnen med fortsättning "
"för varje extra kolumn).</para></listitem> <listitem><para>253 för knappen i "
"rad 4, kolumn 1.</para></listitem> <listitem><para>254 för knappen i rad 4, "
"kolumn 3.</para></listitem> </itemizedlist> Värdena kan definieras om genom "
"att använda kommandot alias, där namnet på knappen i rad x, kolumn y (rader "
"och kolumner börjar på 1), är Keypad_x_y. För att exempelvis ge asterisken "
"på en 4x3 knappsats värdet noll, skulle följande alias användas:"

#. Tag: title
#: microbe.docbook:213
#, no-c-format
msgid "Aliasing a keypad key to a value"
msgstr "Skapa ett alias för en knapp på en knappsats till ett värde"

#. Tag: programlisting
#: microbe.docbook:214
#, no-c-format
msgid "alias Keypad_4_1 0"
msgstr "alias Keypad_4_1 0"

#. Tag: title
#: microbe.docbook:221
#, no-c-format
msgid "PIC I/O"
msgstr "PIC in- och utmatning"

#. Tag: title
#: microbe.docbook:224
#, no-c-format
msgid "Port Direction"
msgstr "Portriktning"

#. Tag: para
#: microbe.docbook:225
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The port direction is set by assigning a value to TRIS*, where * is the port "
"letter. For example:"
msgstr ""
"Portriktningen anges genom att tilldela ett värde till TRIS*, där * är "
"portbokstaven. Exempelvis:"

#. Tag: title
#: microbe.docbook:228
#, no-c-format
msgid "Setting port directions"
msgstr "Ställa in portriktningar"

#. Tag: programlisting
#: microbe.docbook:229
#, no-c-format
msgid "TRISB = b'01111001'"
msgstr "TRISB = b'01111001'"

#. Tag: para
#: microbe.docbook:231
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The above sets pins RB1, RB2 and RB7 on PORTB as outputs, and the other pins "
"on PORTB as inputs. In this example, b'01111001' is a binary representation "
"of the output type. The 1 on the right represents an output on RB0, and the "
"0 on the left represents an input on RB7."
msgstr ""
"Ovanstående ställer in anslutningarna RB1, RB2 och RB7 på PORTB som "
"utgångar, och övriga anslutningar på PORTB som ingångar. I exemplet är "
"b'01111001' den binära representationen av utgångstypen. Värdet 1 till höger "
"representerar en utgång på RB0, och värdet 0 till vänster representerar en "
"ingång på RB7."

#. Tag: title
#: microbe.docbook:237
#, no-c-format
msgid "Port I/O"
msgstr "Port in- och utmatning"

#. Tag: para
#: microbe.docbook:238
#, no-c-format
msgid "The port can be treated as a variable. For example:"
msgstr "Porten kan behandlas som en variabel, exempelvis:"

#. Tag: title
#: microbe.docbook:242
#, no-c-format
msgid "Writing to a port"
msgstr "Skriva till en port"

#. Tag: programlisting
#: microbe.docbook:243
#, no-c-format
msgid "x = PORTA"
msgstr "x = PORTA"

#. Tag: para
#: microbe.docbook:246
#, no-c-format
msgid "The above assigns the value of PORTA to the variable x."
msgstr "Det ovanstående tilldelar värdet av PORTA till variabeln x."

#. Tag: title
#: microbe.docbook:252
#, no-c-format
msgid "Pin I/O"
msgstr "In- och utmatning för anslutningar"

#. Tag: para
#: microbe.docbook:253
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Each pin on a port is obtained by prefixing the pin number by the port name; "
"&eg; Pin 2 (starting from Pin 0) on PORTA is known as <emphasis>PORTA.0</"
"emphasis>. The syntax to set a pin state is: <programlisting role=\"correct"
"\">PORTX.N = <emphasis>STATE</emphasis></programlisting> where "
"<emphasis>STATE</emphasis> can be <emphasis>high</emphasis> or "
"<emphasis>low</emphasis>. The syntax to test a pin state is: <programlisting "
"role=\"correct\"><function>if</function> PORTX.N is <emphasis>STATE</"
"emphasis> <function>then</function></programlisting> Combining these "
"examples, we have:"
msgstr ""
"Varje anslutning i en port erhålls genom att inleda anslutningsnumret med "
"portnamnet: t.ex. anslutning 2 (med början på anslutning 0) på PORTA  kallas "
"<emphasis>PORTA.0</emphasis>. Syntaxen för att ställa in ett tillstånd på en "
"anslutning är: <programlisting role=\"correct\">PORTX.N = <emphasis>STATE</"
"emphasis></programlisting> där <emphasis>STATE</emphasis> kan vara "
"<emphasis>high</emphasis> (hög) eller <emphasis>low</emphasis> (låg). "
"Syntaxen för att testa en anslutnings tillstånd är: <programlisting role="
"\"correct\"><function>if</function> PORTX.N is <emphasis>STATE</"
"emphasis><function>then</function></programlisting> Kombineras exemplen, får "
"vi:"

#. Tag: title
#: microbe.docbook:266
#, no-c-format
msgid "Setting and testing pin state"
msgstr "Ställa in och prova anslutningens tillstånd"

#. Tag: programlisting
#: microbe.docbook:267
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"TRISA = 0\n"
"TRISB = 255\n"
"<function>if</function> PORTA.3 is <function>high</function> <function>then</"
"function>\n"
"{\n"
"        PORTB.5 = <function>low</function>\n"
"}\n"
"<function>else</function>\n"
"{\n"
"        PORTB = PORTA + 15\n"
"}"
msgstr ""
"TRISA = 0\n"
"TRISB = 255\n"
"<function>if</function> PORTA.3 is <function>high</function> <function>then</"
"function>\n"
"{\n"
"        PORTB.5 = <function>low</function>\n"
"}\n"
"<function>else</function>\n"
"{\n"
"        PORTB = PORTA + 15\n"
"}"

#. Tag: title
#: microbe.docbook:273
#, no-c-format
msgid "Variables"
msgstr "Variabler"

#. Tag: para
#: microbe.docbook:274
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"All variables are 8-bit unsigned integers, giving a range from 0 to 255. "
"<application>&microbe;</application> supports the typical unary operations "
"(acting on one variable) and binary operations (acting on two variables) "
"that are supported by the PIC. In addition, &microbe; also supports division "
"and multiplication."
msgstr ""
"Alla variabler är 8-bitars heltal utan tecken, vilket ger intervallet 0 till "
"255. <application>&microbe;</application> stöder de typiska unära (som "
"arbetar med en variabel) och binära (som arbetar med två variabler) "
"operatorerna som stöds av PIC:n. Dessutom stöder &microbe; också division "
"och multiplikation."

#. Tag: title
#: microbe.docbook:280
#, no-c-format
msgid "Unary Operations"
msgstr "Unära operationer"

#. Tag: para
#: microbe.docbook:283
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<emphasis>rotateleft x</emphasis> - Rotates the variable x left through "
"carry."
msgstr ""
"<emphasis>rotateleft x</emphasis> - Roterar variabeln x åt vänster via carry."

#. Tag: para
#: microbe.docbook:284
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<emphasis>rotateright x</emphasis> - Rotates the variable x right through "
"carry."
msgstr ""
"<emphasis>rotateright x</emphasis> - Roterar variabeln x åt höger via carry."

#. Tag: para
#: microbe.docbook:285
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<emphasis>increment x</emphasis> - Increments the variable x. If x has a "
"value of 255, then x wraps round to 0."
msgstr ""
"<emphasis>increment x</emphasis> - Ökar variabeln x med ett. Om x har värdet "
"255, slår den runt till 0."

#. Tag: para
#: microbe.docbook:286
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<emphasis>decrement x</emphasis> - Decrements the variable x. If x has a "
"value of 0, then x wraps round to 255."
msgstr ""
"<emphasis>decrement x</emphasis> - Minskar variabeln x med ett. Om x har "
"värdet 0, slår den runt till 255."

#. Tag: title
#: microbe.docbook:292
#, no-c-format
msgid "Arithmetic"
msgstr "Aritmetik"

#. Tag: para
#: microbe.docbook:293 microbe.docbook:309
#, no-c-format
msgid "Supported operations:"
msgstr "Operationer som stöds:"

#. Tag: para
#: microbe.docbook:296
#, no-c-format
msgid "<emphasis>Addition:</emphasis> x + y"
msgstr "<emphasis>Addition:</emphasis> x + y"

#. Tag: para
#: microbe.docbook:297
#, no-c-format
msgid "<emphasis>Subtraction:</emphasis> x - y"
msgstr "<emphasis>Subtraktion:</emphasis> x - y"

#. Tag: para
#: microbe.docbook:298
#, no-c-format
msgid "<emphasis>Multiplication:</emphasis> x * y"
msgstr "<emphasis>Multiplikation:</emphasis> x * y"

#. Tag: para
#: microbe.docbook:299
#, no-c-format
msgid "<emphasis>Division:</emphasis> x / y"
msgstr "<emphasis>Division:</emphasis> x / y"

#. Tag: para
#: microbe.docbook:300
#, no-c-format
msgid "<emphasis>Binary XOR:</emphasis> x XOR y"
msgstr "<emphasis>Binär exklusiv ELLER:</emphasis> x XOR y"

#. Tag: para
#: microbe.docbook:301
#, no-c-format
msgid "<emphasis>Binary AND:</emphasis> x AND y"
msgstr "<emphasis>Binär OCH:</emphasis> x AND y"

#. Tag: para
#: microbe.docbook:302
#, no-c-format
msgid "<emphasis>Binary OR:</emphasis> x OR y"
msgstr "<emphasis>Binär ELLER:</emphasis> x OR y"

#. Tag: title
#: microbe.docbook:308 microbe.docbook:324
#, no-c-format
msgid "Comparison"
msgstr "Jämförelse"

#. Tag: para
#: microbe.docbook:313
#, no-c-format
msgid "<emphasis>Equals:</emphasis> x == y"
msgstr "<emphasis>Lika med:</emphasis> x == y"

#. Tag: para
#: microbe.docbook:314
#, no-c-format
msgid "<emphasis>Does not equal:</emphasis> x != y"
msgstr "<emphasis>Skilt från:</emphasis> x != y"

#. Tag: para
#: microbe.docbook:315
#, no-c-format
msgid "<emphasis>Is greater than:</emphasis> x > y"
msgstr "<emphasis>Större än:</emphasis> x > y"

#. Tag: para
#: microbe.docbook:316
#, no-c-format
msgid "<emphasis>Is less than:</emphasis> x &lt; y"
msgstr "<emphasis>Mindre än:</emphasis> x &lt; y"

#. Tag: para
#: microbe.docbook:317
#, no-c-format
msgid "<emphasis>Is greater than or equal to:</emphasis> x &gt;= y"
msgstr "<emphasis>Större än eller lika med:</emphasis> x &gt;= y"

#. Tag: para
#: microbe.docbook:318
#, no-c-format
msgid "<emphasis>Is less than or equal to:</emphasis> x &lt;= y"
msgstr "<emphasis>Mindre än eller lika med:</emphasis> x &lt;= y"

#. Tag: para
#: microbe.docbook:321
#, no-c-format
msgid "For example:"
msgstr "Till exempel:"

#. Tag: programlisting
#: microbe.docbook:325
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<function>if</function> PORTA >= 5 <function>then</function>\n"
"{\n"
"        ...\n"
"}"
msgstr ""
"<function>if</function> PORTA >= 5 <function>then</function>\n"
"{\n"
"        ...\n"
"}"

#~ msgid ""
#~ "<application>Microbe</application> compiles programs written in the "
#~ "custom language for PICs, as a companion program to "
#~ "<application>&kappname;</application>. The syntax has been designed to "
#~ "suit a &flowcode; program. The syntax for running <command>microbe</"
#~ "command> from the commandline is: <programlisting>microbe [options] "
#~ "[input.microbe] [output.asm]</programlisting> where options are: "
#~ "<itemizedlist> <listitem><para><function>--show-source</function> - Puts "
#~ "each line of &microbe; source code as a comment in the assembly output "
#~ "before the assembly instructions themselves for that line.</para></"
#~ "listitem> <listitem><para><function>--no-optimize</function> - Prevent "
#~ "optimization of the instructions generated from the source. Optimization "
#~ "is usually safe, and so this option is mainly used for debugging.</para></"
#~ "listitem> </itemizedlist> The .microbe input file must identify the "
#~ "target PIC by inserting the PIC name at the top of the .microbe file; e."
#~ "g. the name of a PIC16F84 is \"P16F84\"."
#~ msgstr ""
#~ "<application>Microbe</application> kompilerar program skrivna i språket "
#~ "anpassat för PIC:er, som ett medföljande program till "
#~ "<application>&kappname;</application>. Syntaxen har skapats för att passa "
#~ "ett &flowcode;-program. Syntaxen för att köra <command>microbe</command> "
#~ "på kommandoraden är: <programlisting>microbe [väljare] [indata.microbe] "
#~ "[utdata.asm]</programlisting> där väljare är: <itemizedlist> "
#~ "<listitem><para><function>--show-source</function>: Lägger till varje "
#~ "&microbe;-källkodsrad  som en kommentar i assemblerutmatningen innan "
#~ "själva assemblerinstruktionerna för den raden.</para></listitem> "
#~ "<listitem><para><function>--no-optimize</function>: Förhindra optimering "
#~ "av instruktionerna skapade från källkoden. Optimering är oftast säker, "
#~ "alltså är väljaren i huvudsak avsedd för avlusning.</para></listitem> </"
